16/07/2010
THE HAGUE, The Netherlands -- The UN war crimes tribunal announced on Thursday (July 15th) that it is granting temporary release to former Chief of General Staff of the Yugoslav Army Momcilo Perisic, for family and humanitarian reasons. 
He will spend time with his ailing wife and with his grandchildren. 
Perisic, who is charged with crimes against humanity and war crimes committed between 1993 and 1995 during the conflicts in Bosnia and Herzegovina and Croatia, will be released on July 23rd and must be back at The Hague on August 19th. 
After surrendering to authorities in 2005, his trial at The Hague began in October 2008. 
(Press Online, Beta, Radio Free Europe - 15/07/10)
